<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>Help - SwagSMP</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <style>
        @font-face {
            font-family: 'MyFont';
            src: url('/MinecraftBold-nMK1.otf') format('opentype');
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body class="bg-gray-900 text-white font-['MyFont'] flex flex-col items-center justify-start min-h-screen p-8">
<h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-center text-purple-400 mt-4">Help & Common Issues</h1>

<div class="bg-gray-800 rounded p-6 mt-6 max-w-2xl space-y-8">
    <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-purple-300">Issue: I put the wrong Minecraft name in</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 mt-2">
            This is fine — simply go through the process again but put the correct name, and it will sort itself out.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-purple-300">Issue: I can't join the server anymore because I'm not a sub</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 mt-2">
            To play on the server, you must be an active subscriber to either
            <a class="text-purple-400" href="https://www.twitch.tv/swag_charhar">swag_charhar</a> or
            <a class="text-purple-400" href="https://www.twitch.tv/unfunnyttv">unfunnyttv</a>.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-purple-300">Issue: I want to play on Bedrock and Java</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 mt-2">
            Simply go through the registration process twice — one for Bedrock and another for Java. It will add both accounts.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-purple-300">Issue: I've subbed but can't join</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 mt-2">
            Please allow at least an hour for the system to add you to the whitelist. It may take some time for your status to be updated.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<a href="/" class="mt-8 text-purple-400 hover:underline">← Back to Main Page</a>
</body>
</html>
